{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc"]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Enhance your content’s presentation with special formatting and styling for text and lists."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/docc\/formatting-your-documentation-content"]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"metadata":{"title":"Formatting Your Documentation Content","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"DocC"}],"role":"article"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Structure-and-Formatting","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/adding-tables-of-data","doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/other-formatting-options","doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/adding-images","doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/adding-structure-to-your-documentation-pages","doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/customizing-the-appearance-of-your-documentation-pages"],"title":"Structure and Formatting","generated":true}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/formatting-your-documentation-content","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/daringfireball.net\/projects\/markdown\/syntax"},{"text":", a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"lightweight markup language, to give structure and style to your documentation.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"DocC includes a custom dialect of Markdown, documentation markup, which","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"extends Markdown’s syntax to include features like symbol linking, improved","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"image support, term lists, and asides.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To ensure consistent structure and styling, use DocC’s documentation markup for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"all of the documentation you write."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Add a Page Title and Section Headers","anchor":"Add-a-Page-Title-and-Section-Headers","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To add a page title, precede the text you want to use with a hash ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"#"},{"type":"text","text":") and a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"space. For the page title of an article or API collection, use plain text only."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"highlight":[],"wrap":100,"copyToClipboard":true,"syntax":"markdown","type":"codeListing","code":["# Getting Started with Sloths"]},{"style":"important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Page titles must be the first line of content in a documentation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"file. One or more empty lines can precede the page title."}]}],"type":"aside","name":"Important"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For the page title of a landing page, enter a symbol link by wrapping the framework’s","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"module name within a set of double backticks (``).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"highlight":[],"wrap":100,"copyToClipboard":true,"syntax":"markdown","type":"codeListing","code":["# ``SlothCreator``"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For a documentation extension file, enter a symbol link by wrapping the path to the symbol","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"within double backticks (``). The path may start with the framework’s module name","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"or with the name of a top-level symbol in the module.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following example shows a documentation extension link starting with a framework module name:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"highlight":[],"wrap":100,"copyToClipboard":true,"syntax":"markdown","type":"codeListing","code":["# ``SlothCreator\/CareSchedule\/Event``"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The following example shows a documentation extension link to the same symbol starting with a top-level symbol name:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"highlight":[],"wrap":100,"copyToClipboard":true,"syntax":"markdown","type":"codeListing","code":["# ``CareSchedule\/Event``"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Augment every page title with a short and concise single-sentence abstract or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"summary that provides additional information about the content. Add the summary","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"using a new paragraph directly below the page title.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"highlight":[],"wrap":100,"copyToClipboard":true,"syntax":"markdown","type":"codeListing","code":["# Getting Started with Sloths","","Create a sloth and assign personality traits and abilities."]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To add a header for an Overview or a Discussion section, use a double hash"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"##"},{"type":"text","text":") and a space, and then include either term in plain text."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"highlight":[],"wrap":100,"copyToClipboard":true,"syntax":"markdown","type":"codeListing","code":["## Overview"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For all other section headers, use a triple hash ("},{"code":"###","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":") and a space, and then"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"add the title of the header in plain text."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"highlight":[],"wrap":100,"copyToClipboard":true,"syntax":"markdown","type":"codeListing","code":["### Create a Sloth"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this type of section header in framework landing pages, top-level pages,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"articles, and occasionally in symbol reference pages where you need to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"provide more detail."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Format Text in Bold, Italics, and Code Voice","anchor":"Format-Text-in-Bold-Italics-and-Code-Voice","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"DocC provides three ways to format the text in your documentation. You can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"apply bold or italic styling, or you can use code voice, which renders the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specified text in a monospace font."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To add bold styling, wrap the text in a pair of double asterisks (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"**"},{"text":").","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Alternatively, use double underscores (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"__"},{"text":").","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following example uses bold styling for the names of the sloths:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"highlight":[],"wrap":100,"copyToClipboard":true,"syntax":"markdown","type":"codeListing","code":["**Super Sloth**: Likes to eat sticks.","__Silly Sloth__: Prefers twigs for breakfast."]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use italicized text to introduce new or alternative terms to the reader. To add","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"italic styling, wrap the text in a set of single underscores (","type":"text"},{"code":"_","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") or single","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"asterisks (","type":"text"},{"code":"*","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":").","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following example uses italics for the words "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"metabolism"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"habitat"}]},{"text":":","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"markdown","copyToClipboard":true,"code":["A sloth's _metabolism_ is highly dependent on its *habitat*."],"wrap":100,"highlight":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use code voice to refer to symbols inline, or to include short code fragments,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as class names or method signatures.  To add code voice, wrap the text in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a set of backticks (`)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the following example, DocC renders the words "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"ice","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"fire"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"wind"}]},{"type":"text","text":", and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"lightning"}]},{"type":"text","text":" in a monospace font:"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"markdown","copyToClipboard":true,"code":["If your sloth possesses one of the special powers: `ice`, `fire`, ","`wind`, or `lightning`."],"wrap":100,"highlight":[]},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To include multiple lines of code, use a code listing instead. For more","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"information, see ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/formatting-your-documentation-content#Add-Code-Listings","type":"reference"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"level":3,"anchor":"Add-Code-Listings","type":"heading","text":"Add Code Listings"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"DocC includes support for code listings, or fenced code blocks, which allow you"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to go beyond the basic declaration sections you find in symbol reference pages,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and to provide more complete code examples for adopters of your framework. You can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"include code listings in your in-source symbol documentation, in extension"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"files, and in articles and tutorials."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To create a code listing, start a new paragraph and add three backticks","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(```). Then, directly following the backticks, add the name of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"programming language in lowercase text. Add one or more lines of code, and then","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"add a new line and terminate the code listing by adding another three backticks:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"markdown","copyToClipboard":true,"code":["```swift","struct Sightseeing: Activity {","    func perform(with sloth: inout Sloth) -> Speed {","        sloth.energyLevel -= 10","        return .slow","    }","}","```"],"wrap":100,"highlight":[]},{"type":"aside","style":"important","name":"Important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When formatting your code listing, use spaces to indent lines"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"instead of tabs so that DocC preserves the indentation when compiling your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"documentation."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"DocC uses the programming language you specify to apply the correct syntax","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"color formatting. For the example above, DocC generates the following:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","copyToClipboard":true,"code":["struct Sightseeing: Activity {","    func perform(with sloth: inout Sloth) -> Speed {","        sloth.energyLevel -= 10","        return .slow","    }","}"],"wrap":100,"highlight":[]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following table lists the names of the programming languages you can specify"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to enable syntax highlighting for a particular code listing. Each language may"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"have one or more aliases."}]},{"rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Name"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Aliases"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"bash"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"sh, zsh"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"c"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"h","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"cpp"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"cc, c++, h++, hpp, hh, hxx, cxx","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"css","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"diff"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"patch","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"http"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"https","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"java"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"jsp","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"javascript"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"js, jsx, mjs, cjs"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"json","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"llvm"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"markdown","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"md, mkdown, mkd"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"objective-c"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"mm, objc, obj-c, objectivec"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"perl","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"pl, pm"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"php"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"python","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"py, gyp, ipython","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"ruby"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"rb, gemspec, podspec, thor, irb"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"scss","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"shell"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"console, shellsession","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"swift","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"xml","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"html, xhtml, rss, atom, xjb, xsd, xsl, plist, wsf, svg","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"yaml","type":"text"}]}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"yml"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"header":"row","type":"table"},{"text":"Add Bulleted, Numbered, and Term Lists","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Add-Bulleted-Numbered-and-Term-Lists"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"DocC supports the following list types:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"header":"row","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Type"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Usage","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Bulleted list","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Groups items that can appear in any order."}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Numbered list","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Delineates a sequence of events in a particular order."}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Term list","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Defines a series of term-definition pairs.","type":"text"}]}]]],"type":"table"},{"style":"important","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Don’t add images or code listings between list items. Bulleted and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"numbered lists must contain two or more items."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Important","type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To create a bulleted list, precede each of the list’s items with an asterisk (","type":"text"},{"code":"*","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") and a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"space. Alternatively, use a dash (","type":"text"},{"code":"-","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") or a plus sign (","type":"text"},{"code":"+","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") instead of an asterisk (","type":"text"},{"code":"*","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"); the list markers are interchangeable.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"copyToClipboard":true,"code":["* Ice","- Fire","* Wind","+ Lightning"],"wrap":100,"syntax":"markdown","type":"codeListing","highlight":[]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To create a numbered list, precede each of the list’s items with the number of the step, then a period ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"."},{"type":"text","text":") and a space."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"copyToClipboard":true,"code":["1. Give the sloth some food.","2. Take the sloth for a walk.","3. Read the sloth a story.","4. Put the sloth to bed."],"wrap":100,"syntax":"markdown","type":"codeListing","highlight":[]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To create a term list, precede each term with a dash ("},{"code":"-","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":") and a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"space, the "},{"code":"term","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" keyword, and another space. Then add a colon ("},{"code":":","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"), a space, and the definition after the term."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"copyToClipboard":true,"code":["- term Ice: Ice sloths thrive below freezing temperatures.","- term Fire: Fire sloths thrive at boiling temperatures.","- term Wind: Wind sloths thrive at soaring altitudes.","- term Lightning: Lightning sloths thrive in stormy climates."],"wrap":100,"syntax":"markdown","type":"codeListing","highlight":[]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A list item’s text, including terms and their definitions, can use the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"style attributes as other text, and include links to other content, including"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"symbols."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"references":{"doc://org.swift.docc/documentation/docc/formatting-your-documentation-content#Add-Code-Listings":{"title":"Add Code Listings","url":"\/documentation\/docc\/formatting-your-documentation-content#Add-Code-Listings","abstract":[],"kind":"section","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc\/formatting-your-documentation-content#Add-Code-Listings"},"doc://org.swift.docc/documentation/docc":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.docc\/documentation\/docc","type":"topic","title":"Do